 Historical Discord Bot

Overview
This is a simple Discord bot written in Go that provides historical information based on user queries. The bot queries a historical information API to retrieve an event of the day.

 Usage
1. Clone the repository.
2. Replace the placeholder `YOUR_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN` in the `Token` constant with your Discord bot token.
3. Run the bot using the command `go run main.go`.

 Dependencies
- [github.com/bwmarrin/discordgo](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/bwmarrin/discordgo): DiscordGo is a Go module for interacting with the Discord API.
  
 Configuration
- **Token:** Replace the `YOUR_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN` constant with your Discord bot token.
- **APIEndpoint:** The historical information API endpoint is set to [http://history.muffinlabs.com/date](http://history.muffinlabs.com/date).

 Commands
- `!historical [query]`: Retrieves historical information based on the provided query.

Example
If a user sends the message `!historical today`, the bot will query the historical information API and respond with an event of the day.

Note
- This bot is a simple example and may require additional error handling and improvements for production use.
- The JSON response parsing is done using string manipulation for simplicity. Consider using a JSON decoding library for a more robust solution.

Feel free to contribute and enhance the functionality of this Discord bot!